{
  "id": 6234471210811392,
  "name": "CSS background-clip: border-area",
  "summary": "Implements the border-area value for the CSS background-clip property, as defined in CSS Backgrounds Level 4. background-clip: border-area clips an element's background to the area painted by its border strokes, taking border-width and border-style into account while ignoring transparency from border-color. This enables gradient borders without border-image. WebKit already ships this feature; this implementation brings Chromium to parity.",
