  "motivation": "There is currently no ergonomic way to clip a background to the visible border geometry in CSS. Authors who want gradient or image borders must use border-image, which is complex, overrides other border styling, and does not compose well with other properties. The border-area clip value provides a clean, declarative solution to this problem. WebKit already ships this feature, and it is part of the actively developed CSS Backgrounds Level 4 specification.",
